{"id":87117,"date":"2020-10-08T10:20:48","date_gmt":"2020-10-08T00:20:48","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/?p=87117"},"modified":"2021-12-03T17:04:41","modified_gmt":"2021-12-03T07:04:41","slug":"state-territory-nomination-interim-allocation","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/state-territory-nomination-interim-allocation\/","title":{"rendered":"State and Territory Nomination Interim Allocation"},"content":{"rendered":"[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][vc_column_text]The State &amp; Territory nomination program\u00a0is<strong> temporarily closed<\/strong> until the Commonwealth Government\u2019s allocation of state nomination places for 2020-21 takes place as part of the Federal budget process (6 October 2020).<\/p>\n<p>However, some States and Territories have been provided with a <strong>limited number of <\/strong>interim allocation <strong>places<\/strong> for the following programs:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>General Skilled Migration &#8211; <strong>State and Territory nomination<\/strong><\/li>\n<li>Business Migration<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>The nomination process will be dependent on each State and Territory Government, and applications will be prioritised based on skills and sectors critical to supporting the country\u2019s response to the COVID19 pandemic.<\/p>\n<p>Critical skills, services, and sectors include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Critical or specialist <strong>medical services<\/strong>, such as air ambulance, medical evacuations, and delivering critical medical supplies.<\/li>\n<li>Critical skills required to maintain the <strong>supply of essential goods and services<\/strong>, such as in medical technology, critical infrastructure, telecommunications, engineering and mining, supply chain logistics, agricultural technology, food production, and the maritime industry.<\/li>\n<li>Services in sectors <strong>critical to Australia\u2019s economic recovery<\/strong> such as financial technology, large scale manufacturing, film and television production, and emerging technology.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>According to the above, some States\/Territories have now published relevant skills occupation lists and requirements for the interim period. See below a summary table representing the current status:<\/p>\n<table class=\"hrow\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\" width=\"100%\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\"><strong>State\/Territory<\/strong><\/td>\n<td width=\"180\"><strong>List \/ Requirements<\/strong><\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><strong>Status<\/strong><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\"><strong>Effective date<\/strong><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">Australian Capital Territory<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.canberrayourfuture.com.au\/portal\/migrating\/article\/act-critical-skills-list\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ACT Critical Skills List<\/a><br \/>\nCanberra residents only.<\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: green; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">OPEN<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\">19\/08\/2020<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">New South Wales<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\">Only for applicants currently in selected health, ICT and engineering occupations. Only visa subclass 190. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.business.nsw.gov.au\/live-and-work-in-nsw\/visas-and-immigration\/skilled-visas\/Skilled-Nominated-visa-subclass-190\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Read more<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: #ff854b; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">MAY BE OPEN<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\">The program may be open however the website is not updated.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">Northern Territory<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\"><\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: red; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">CLOSED<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">Queensland<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\">Only critical skills and onshore applicants<\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: #ff854b; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">SUSPENDED<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\">May re-open again in December 2020<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">South Australia<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\">All occupations on the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/mltssl\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">MLTSSL<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/stsol\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">STSOL<\/a> or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/rol\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ROL<\/a> are eligible for nomination. However, you need to satisfy the <a href=\"https:\/\/migration.sa.gov.au\/skilled-migrants\/supporting-information\/state-nomination-requirements\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SA requirements listed here<\/a>.<\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: green; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">OPEN<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\">27\/08\/2020<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">Tasmania<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\">Applicants in\u00a0critical roles\u00a0may be nominated. Check the specified <a href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/tasmania-skilled-migration-interim-allocations\/\">critical skills here<\/a>.<\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: green; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">OPEN<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\">25\/08\/2020<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">Victoria<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\">Only for applicants working in\u00a0health or medical research and are contributing to Victoria\u2019s economic recovery and\/or health response. <a href=\"https:\/\/liveinmelbourne.vic.gov.au\/migrate\/skilled-migration-visas\/2020-21-skilled-migration-visa-nomination-program\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Read more<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: green; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">OPEN<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\">08\/09\/2020<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"100\">Western Australia<\/td>\n<td width=\"101\">WA Migration Services will not issue invitations to apply for State nomination during the suspension period. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.migration.wa.gov.au\/services\/skilled-migration-western-australia\/latest-news\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Read more<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"100\"><span style=\"background-color: #ff854b; color: #fff; padding: 5px 15px;\">SUSPENDED<\/span><\/td>\n<td width=\"108\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p><strong>Critical skills &amp; sectors<\/strong> specified by the Department of Home Affairs:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/covid19.homeaffairs.gov.au\/critical-skills-and-sectors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https:\/\/covid19.homeaffairs.gov.au\/critical-skills-and-sectors<\/a>[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;20&#8243;][nectar_global_section id=&#8221;109315&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221;&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":109514,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[90,25,129],"tags":[],"class_list":{"0":"post-87117","1":"post","2":"type-post","3":"status-publish","4":"format-standard","5":"has-post-thumbnail","7":"category-occupation-list","8":"category-news","9":"category-skilled-visa"},"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/87117","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{